        <h2>RevWood Premier vs COREtec: What the flooring salesperson won't tell you</h2>
        <p class="post-card-deck">Both claim waterproof. Both look like hardwood. One is genuinely harder and costs 20% less. The other handles a wet basement without a single asterisk. A field-honest comparison — room by room.</p>
